9 An Act relating to professions and occupations;
amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1688, as amended by
10 Section 3, Chapter 355, O.S.L. 2024 (59 O.S. Supp.
2025, Section 1688), which relates to term of license
11 and registration certificates; prohibiting certain
expired license from being renewed; allowing certain
12 expired license to be reinstated; requiring certain
former licensee to submit certain application;
13 requiring certain application to include certain
information; exempting certain licensee from certain
14 continuing education requirements for certain time
period; requiring certain licensee to complete
15 certain continuing education requirement within
certain time period; updating statutory language; and
16 providing an effective date.
17
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
20 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1688, as
21 amended by Section 3, Chapter 355, O.S.L. 2024 (59 O.S. Supp. 2025,
22 Section 1688), is amended to read as follows:
23 Section 1688. A. No license shall be issued for longer than
24 one (1) year, and all licenses shall expire on the last day in the
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3673 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 birt h month of the licensee. A license may be renewed upon
2 application and payment of fees thirty (30) days preceding or
3 following the date the license is due. Licenses renewed more than
4 thirty (30) days following the date of expiration may be renewed
5 only upon application and payment of all required fees and payment
6 of any penalty for late renewal established by the Construction
7 Industries Board and upon compliance with any applicable continuing
8 education requirements established by the Board and the Electrical
9 License Act. No penalty for late renewal shall be charged to any
10 holder of a license which expires while the holder is in military
11 service, if an application for renewal is made within one (1) year
12 following the service discharge of the holder.
13 B. No journeyman or contractor license shall be renewed unless
14 the licensee has completed the required hours of continuing
15 education, pursuant to the Electrical License Act and as determined
16 and approved by the Committee of Electrical Examiners and approved
17 by the Construction Industries Board.
18 C. Any license that remains expired for longer than one (1)
19 year shall not be renewed but shall be reinstated pursuant to this
20 subsection when compliant with all license requirements. To obtain
21 the license formerly held, the former license holder shall be
22 required to submit a reinstatement application provided by the Board
23 and either retest or satisfy all of the following:
24 1. Submit a complete reinstatement application to the Board;
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3673 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 2. Pay the standard license renewal fee and a reinstatement
2 penalty fee of Two Hundred Dollars ($200.00);
3 3. Submit certification of completion within the preceding
4 twelve-month period of all continuing education approved by the
5 Committee of Electrical Examiners as follows:
6 a. if the applicant has satisfied the continuing
7 education requirements required for license renewal
8 within the preceding thirty-six (36) months, no
9 additional continuing education shall be required, or
10 b. if the license has been expired for more than thirty-
11 six (36) months, the applicant shall complete twelve
12 (12) hours of continuing education for each full
13 thirty-six-month period the license has remained
14 expired, not to exceed twenty-four (24) hours; and
15 4. Submit an original sworn affidavit or other verification
16 satisfactory to the Board that the applicant has not been subject to
17 final disciplinary action that would preclude licensure and has not
18 been convicted of a crime that has a direct bearing on the
19 applicant’s fitness to practice as an electrician.
20 D. A licensee shall be exempt from the continuing education
21 requirements for license renewal for three (3) years from the date
22 the licensee passed his or her current licensing exam.
23 E. A licensee whose license was reinstated through the option
24 of completing the required hours of continuing education in lieu of
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB3673 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 rete sting after being expired for more than one (1) year shall, for
2 the first timely submitted license renewal of the reinstated
3 license, complete the continuing education required pursuant to this
4 section for renewing his or her license within thirty-six (36)
5 months beginning from the date of the last verified continuing
6 education course completed for reinstatement of an expired license.
7 F. An apprentice registration certificate shall be issued for
8 one (1) year, at which time the apprentice may reregister upon
9 meeting the requirements of the Construction Industries Board and
10 paying the renewal fee.
11 D. G. A student apprentice registration certificate shall be
12 issued for the registrant’s school year. A student apprentice
13 registration expires on the last day of the registrant’s school
14 year, at which time the apprentice may reregister upon meeting the
15 requirements of the Construction Industries Board and paying the
16 renewal fee.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
